entries.meaning: (archaic or fantasy) The person in charge of a house; a housekeeper or innkeeper.
examples: The housekeep was back rather quickly with a tray, which held a flagon of ale and a pewter cup as well as bread and cheese.

verbs.description: housekeep (third-person singular simple present housekeeps, present participle housekeeping, simple past and past participle housekept)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To carry out the domestic duties of housekeeping.
(transitive, intransitive, computing) To perform the general tasks of housekeeping.
examples: The clock burst which enables the supervisor to housekeep the console input and output and to change program status is currently set to 200 ms.
